<p>The United States is preparing a new phase of operations targeting Venezuela in the coming days, as President Trump increases pressure on President Nicolás Maduro’s government, though the exact timing and scope remain undecided, according to multiple U.S. officials cited by media outlets [scmp.com#1][dawn.com#1][thehindu.com#1]. Options under discussion include covert actions as an initial step and, among the possibilities, attempting to overthrow Maduro, while the administration frames its effort as part of a push to combat illegal drugs; Maduro denies any drug links [dawn.com#1][scmp.com#1][thehindu.com#1]. U.S. discussions have also included dropping information leaflets over Caracas as psychological pressure ramps up [cbsnews.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/eC-R_Sfd9mNtL49quOuzgiTO3YydCKNPCV7kMedmMB5TjXvNkLTeA4TBPYVOg6yBaxZsKPZ0nTOvl1LEL4nqyStpPRnEvPAby9ItBa8dqxev' alt='A Venezuelan Navy coast guard vessel operates off the Caribbean coast near Puerto Cabello.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>New phase planned: U.S. officials say Washington is poised to launch a fresh phase of Venezuela-related operations in the coming days, with details and final decisions still unconfirmed [scmp.com#1][dawn.com#1][thehindu.com#1].</li><li>Covert start: Two U.S. officials indicated covert operations would likely be the first component of any new action against Maduro’s government [dawn.com#1][scmp.com#1].</li><li>Regime-change option: Officials told outlets that options under consideration include attempting to overthrow Maduro, though no final decision has been made [dawn.com#1][thehindu.com#1][scmp.com#1].</li><li>Psyops tactic: The U.S. has considered dropping leaflets over Caracas to increase psychological pressure on Maduro’s circle and security forces [cbsnews.com#1].</li><li>Official posture: The administration says President Trump is prepared to use all elements of American power to curb drug flows; Caracas denies drug-trade links and accuses Washington of seeking to oust Maduro [dawn.com#1].</li></ul><blockquote>President Trump is prepared to use every element of American power to stop drugs from flooding into our country and to bring those responsible to justice. - Senior administration official (anonymous)</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>U.S. administration: Officials say the President is ready to use all elements of American power to stop drugs from entering the U.S. and bring perpetrators to justice [dawn.com#1]. (<a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1956866/us-to-launch-new-phase-of-venezuela-operations-sources-say'>Dawn</a>)</li><li>Venezuelan government: Maduro denies any links to drug trafficking and argues Washington is seeking to oust him, saying Venezuelans and the military will resist such attempts [dawn.com#1]. (<a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1956866/us-to-launch-new-phase-of-venezuela-operations-sources-say'>Dawn</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/united-states-canada/article/3333827/toppling-maduro-among-us-options-trump-set-expand-venezuela-operations'>Toppling Maduro among options as Trump set to expand Venezuela operations</a> - scmp.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1956866/us-to-launch-new-phase-of-venezuela-operations-sources-say'>US to launch new phase of Venezuela operations, sources say</a> - dawn.com</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/us-to-launch-new-phase-of-venezuela-operations-sources-say/article70313474.ece'>U.S. to launch new phase of Venezuela operations, sources say</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.cbsnews.com/news/u-s-considers-dropping-leaflets-venezuela-maduro/'>U.S. considers dropping leaflets in Venezuela as it ramps up pressure on Maduro</a> - cbsnews.com</li></ul>